                         <head>Miscellaneous works on ritual prayer, 2 items (a-b)</head>
                         <msContents
                              class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2010108002 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2007003439">
                              <summary>Miscellaneous collection consisting primarily of a work on
                                   ritual prayer. Volume not dated; datable to the sixteenth and
                                   eighteenth century. Neat scribal Persian naskh. Annotations in
                                   margins. Stamped and (partially preserved) Persian foliation.
                                   Lacking original binding. Binding, red half leather IOL covers,
                                   stamp dated 14 May 1916. Folios bound, but occasionally
                                   disarranged; cropped, wormholes, water stains, later repairs;
                                   gauze overlay over large numbers of folios. Condition fragile. </summary>
                              <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic </textLang>
                              <msItem n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_122-item1">
                                   <locus from="1v" to="108r">ff. 1v-108r </locus>
                                   <textLang mainLang="ar" otherLangs="fa">Arabic and Persian </textLang>
                                   <note><p>Delhi Persian 122 a. </p><p>Compendious treatise on the
                                             ritual prayers and other religious duties by <persName
                                                  key="person_f8092" role="aut">Abū Bakr Aḥmad ibn
                                                  Muḥammad ibn ʿAlī al-Qurashī or Qarshī</persName>.
                                             </p><p>Arabic and Qur’anic quotations overlined;
                                             headings in red. </p><p>Not dated at end. Datable to
                                             the sixteenth century. </p><p>Although cropped, folio
                                             82 retains its original dimension along the lower edge.
                                        </p></note>
                                   <author><persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f8092">Abū
                                             Bakr Aḥmad ibn Muḥammad ibn ʿAlī
                                             al-Qarshī</persName><persName xml:lang="fa"
                                             key="person_f8092">ابو بكر احمد ابن محمّد ابن على
                                             القرشى</persName></author>
                                   <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_22065">Navāfil
                                        al-masāʾil</title>
                                   <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_22065">نوافل المسائل</title>
                              </msItem>
                              <msItem n="2" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_122-item2">
                                   <locus from="110v" to="112v">ff. 110v-112v </locus>
                                   <note><p>Delhi Persian 122 b. </p><p>Untitled selection of two
                                             separate chronogrammatic qiṭaʿāt encoding the ʿurs or
                                             date of death (in 1012/1603) for the Naqshbandī Sufi
                                             saint, <persName
                                                  key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164657139.0x000001 viaf_314814912"
                                                  role="subject">Khvājah Muḥammad Bāqī Billāh
                                                  Dihlavī</persName>. </p><p>Not dated at end.
                                             Datable to the eighteenth century. </p></note>
                                   <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and
                                        Arabic</textLang>
                                   <note/>
                              </msItem>
